# AuraHub AI Agent Instructions & Guidelines

## Project Context
You are working on AuraHub, a cross-platform desktop GUI application acting as a visual alternative to CLI AI agents (like Claude Code). 
The killer feature is the "Time Machine": a local rollback engine that tracks AI actions and can atomically revert file system changes.

## Tech Stack & Project Structure
- Language: C++20
- Build System: CMake
- Frontend (Client): Qt 6 (Widgets), SQLite (Qt SQL)
- Backend (Server): userver framework, PostgreSQL
- Core Library: AuraMCP (Local Model Context Protocol implementation)

## Architectural Boundaries (STRICT)

### 1. Client App (/client)
- Pattern: strictly MVP (Model-View-Presenter).
- View: Dumb Qt Widgets (QAbstractTableModel, QSortFilterProxyModel). NO business logic or database calls here.
- Model: Contains McpEngine (AI execution), LocalDbService (SQLite), and NetworkGateway (REST HTTP). 
- Rollback Engine: All file modifications made by AI MUST be backed up to the local SQLite database as diffs/blobs *before* execution.
- Network: The client NEVER connects to PostgreSQL directly. All cloud synchronization goes through the userver REST API.

### 2. Server App (/server)
- Framework: userver ONLY. No blocking I/O operations.
- Responsibility: Auth (JWT), storing secure password hashes (Bcrypt/SHA-3), LLM API Proxying, and user settings sync.

### 3. AuraMCP Core (/mcp)
- Concurrency: Lock-free execution phase. Do NOT use std::mutex in hot paths (execute, read). State is immutable after initialization.
- Error Handling: NO runtime exceptions. Do NOT throw std::out_of_range or json::parse_error. Use ToolResult structures with isError = true.
- Parsing: Use the custom jsonrpc::JsonRpcParser with std::variant and std::visit. Do not use raw nlohmann::json parsing in the router.
- Transport: StdioTransport::start() MUST be blocking (run in the main thread loop) to prevent immediate process termination.

## Coding Style
- Follow the Google C++ Style Guide.
- Use .clang-format rules.
- Memory: Use smart pointers (std::unique_ptr, std::shared_ptr) for business logic. Raw pointers are ONLY acceptable for Qt objects managed by the QObject parent-child tree.

## Self-Correction & Error Memory Loop (CRITICAL)
Before writing code or debugging, you MUST review the docs/MEMEX_ERRORS.md file to avoid repeating past mistakes.
If you encounter a new error, bug, or architectural friction more than once, you MUST automatically update docs/MEMEX_ERRORS.md with the symptom, cause, and established solution. Do not ask for permission to update the memex, just do it.